TY  - JOUR
T1  - Dynamic Correction in Marketing Planning Models
AU  - Weinberg, Charles B.
Y1  - 1976/02/01
PY  - 1976
DA  - 1976/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.22.6.677
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.22.6.677
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 677
EP  - 687
VL  - 22
IS  - 6
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Most marketing planning models have carry-over effects in which one period's decisions influence the results obtained in future periods. In this paper it is shown that failure to allow for the carry-over effect beyond the planning horizon can result in underallocation of resources and in biases in the timing pattern of resource expenditure. For a wide class of market planning models, a procedure is developed to take into account this long-term effect. The distortion and the procedure are illustrated in an example.
AB  - Most marketing planning models have carry-over effects in which one period's decisions influence the results obtained in future periods. In this paper it is shown that failure to allow for the carry-over effect beyond the planning horizon can result in underallocation of resources and in biases in the timing pattern of resource expenditure. For a wide class of market planning models, a procedure is developed to take into account this long-term effect. The distortion and the procedure are illustrated in an example.
SN  - 0025-1909
M3  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.22.6.677
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1287/mnsc.22.6.677
Y2  - 2024/03/27
